{"id":"2303.00100","submitter":"Ethan Ackelsberg","authors":"Ethan Ackelsberg and Vitaly Bergelson","title":"Asymptotic total ergodicity for actions of $F[t]$ and\n  Furstenberg--S\\'{a}rk\\\"{o}zy-type theorems over finite fields and rings","comments":"22 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.NT math.DS","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  In the setting of $F[t]$, where $F$ is a finite field, a version of the\nFurstenberg--S\\'{a}rk\\\"{o}zy theorem states that for any $\\delta > 0$, any\nsubset $A$ of the quotient ring $F[t]/Q(t)F[t]$ of density at least $\\delta$\nwill contain distinct elements $a, b \\in A$ with $b-a = P(y)$ for some $y$,\nwhenever $Q$ is of sufficiently high degree.\n  In this paper, we obtain refinements of this result via the phenomenon of\n\\emph{asymptotic total ergodicity} for the quotient rings $F[t]/Q(t)F[t]$.\n(This phenomenon of asymptotic total ergodicity is analogous to the phenomenon\nexplored by Bergelson and Best in the framework of modular rings\n$\\mathbb{Z}/N\\mathbb{Z}$.) In particular, we show that if the minimal degree of\nthe irreducible factors of $Q_n$ diverges to infinity, then for a wide class of\npolynomials $P(y) \\in (F[t])[y]$, the following refinement of the\nFurstenberg--S\\'{a}rk\\\"{o}zy theorem holds: for any $\\delta > 0$, for any two\nsubsets $A, B \\subseteq F[t]/Q_n(t)F[t]$ with $|A| |B| \\ge \\delta\n|F[t]/Q_n(t)F[t]|^2$ and $n$ sufficiently large, there exist $x, y \\in\nF[t]/Q_n(t)F[t]$ such that $x \\in A$ and $x + P(y) \\in B$. Moreover, the values\n$x, y \\in F[t]/Q_n(t)F[t]$ for which $x \\in A$ and $x + P(y) \\in B$ obey the\n\"correct\" statistical behavior as $n \\to \\infty$. The class of polynomials\n$P(y)$ for which this result holds is characterized by equidistributional\nbehavior previously studied by Bergelson and Leibman. We also show that, in the\nabsence of asymptotic total ergodicity and a natural equidistribution\ncondition, one cannot hope for such a refinement to the\nFurstenberg--S\\'{a}rk\\\"{o}zy theorem.\n  Another consequence of our results is a power saving bound for the\nFurstenberg--S\\'{a}rk\\\"{o}zy theorem over finite fields of fixed characterstic.\nThis complements recent work of Li and Sauermann, where a different power\nsaving bound is obtained using the polynomial method.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Feb 2023 21:59:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-02"}
